# VibeCart — always deploy (sync) after material changes

**Mandatory final step:** When this rule applies, **always** end by running **`npm run deploy`** from **`vibecart/`** in the terminal—even if you only changed one file, even if mirrors look fine, even if Netlify runs sync in CI. Local mirrors must never lag the canonical tree you edited.

**Default:** After **any** edit that affects the static site or mobile shell (HTML, CSS, client JS, `mobile-app-shell.js`, `service-worker.js`, root assets mirrored to `deploy-web/` / `vibecart-netlify/`), **always** run deploy sync before you stop. Do not hand off with root updated but mirrors stale.

1. From **`vibecart/`** repo root, run **`npm run deploy`** (alias for **`npm run deploy:sync`** and **`npm run build`**) so `deploy-web/` and `vibecart-netlify/` match sources.
2. To sync **and** commit **and** push in one step: **`npm run ship -- "clear message"`** (ship runs deploy sync first).
3. If you commit manually: **`git add`** all intended paths (including sync outputs), **`git commit`**, **`git push origin`** (usually `main`) so Netlify/deploy stay current.

Do **not** leave production-bound fixes only in root while `deploy-web/` is old. Do **not** `git push --force` unless the user explicitly asks.

If the user said **not** to push yet, still run **`npm run deploy`** locally and say the tree is ready; skip push only then.
